snippet: The members of  the Five Star Movement called for the occupation to demand permanent parliamentary committees, even though no party has yet produced a governing majority.
abstract: Members of Beppe Grillo's Five Star Movement stage occupation of Italian Parliament, odd action considering that they control163 of its 945 seats; movement demands permanent parliamentary committees, even though no party has yet produced governing majority.
lead_paragraph: The members of  the Five Star Movement called for the occupation to demand permanent parliamentary committees, even though no party has yet produced a governing majority.

headline.seo: In Italy, an ‘Occupation’ of Parliament Amid Political Gridlock
headline.main: Upstart Party in Italy ‘Occupies’ a Parliament That Is Already Paralyzed
headline.print_headline: Upstart Party in Italy ‘Occupies’ a Parliament That Is Already Paralyzed
